{
  "texts": [
    "QLoRA achieves this by applying four-bit quantization to the LLM and enabling backpropagation of gradients through these quantized, frozen layers, significantly improving efficiency without sacrificing performance.",
    "The creation of a requirements list is a text-based activity, making it highly suitable for the application of NLP models.",
    "LLMs can assist in extracting relevant information from extensive pre-trained datasets while addressing ambiguities and inconsistencies.",
    "This ensures that requirements are clear, structured, and well-aligned with product development needs by converting project-specific language into formal notations (Bertram et al., 2022) and machine-readable formats (Ray et al., 2023).",
    "While prompt engineering serves as an alternative to fine-tuning for requirements elicitation, it is highly dependent on precise wording."
  ]
}